  "caption": "Ever wondered what happens between your schematic and a finished PCB?\n\nHere's the complete 8 step workflow, from concept to quality tested board.\n\n1. Requirements: Define specs with your full team.\n2. Schematic: Capture electrical connections as your blueprint.\n3. Placement: Position components for signal flow and thermals.\n4. Routing: Trace paths, copper pours, impedance matching.\n5. Verification: DRC and DFM checks catch errors before fab.\n6. File Generation: Gerbers, drill files, BOM, all production data.\n7. Fabrication: Etching, lamination, drilling, plating, finishing.\n8. Quality: AOI, electrical testing, visual inspection.\n\nSkipping any of these steps costs you time and money downstream.\n\nAt Cu Circuits, every board goes through this full pipeline with rigorous DFM review built in.\n\nSave this as your PCB workflow checklist.\n\n#PCB #PCBDesign #PCBFabrication #CuCircuits #HardwareEngineering #Electronics #MakeInIndia",
